<p>After this, whenever anything gets put in that folder, the system will alert you that something has been placed in your widgets directory and ask if you want to see it. If you werenâ€™t expecting this, say if you visited the zaptastic site and got â€œdrive-by-downloadedâ€ youâ€™ll at least get tipped to the situation and can either examine the contents of the widget (if youâ€™re a geek like me) or trash it without having to dig through anything. You could also go another step and have Applescript check the contents for certain keys within the widget (say looking for preferences that allow full system access) but I think this will suffice for most people until Apple addresses the problem head on.</p>

